bug.short_desc: very long and/or multiline error messages are not displayed correctly

long_desc.thetext: When a connector returns a very long and/or multiline error message, it is not displayed correctly in the task editor. The header of the task editor can become very large, and there is a huge flickering tooltip when hovering over it.

Created attachment 229306 screenshot
In this case, the error message was a very long stack trace.
I have seen this problem as well. Not sure it's helpful to have a stack trace in the message but the framework should handle this better regardless.

(In reply to comment #1) > Created attachment 229306 > screenshot > > In this case, the error message was a very long stack trace.
Do you know the kind of the stack trace.

Here an review https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/11706/
the message is now limited to 100 char.

Thanks Frank. This change fixes the problem for me. But I wonder if we should ensure that there are no linebreaks in the message too. Also, 100 chars seems a bit short (even shorter than a Twitter message!). Maybe 256 would be a better choice.
There is another problem I didn't mention though: when clicking on the error message, I get a huge dialog that fills my screen. Maybe we should make a similar change in displayStatus.
